# ADR-004: PostgreSQL Vector Storage

## Status

Accepted

## Context

Semantic search requires persistent storage for embeddings.

The project requires a database solution that supports vector similarity operations.

## Decision

PostgreSQL will be used as the initial persistence layer with vector capabilities.

Database access will be isolated through:

services/dbConnector.ts

## Consequences

Positive:

- Mature database ecosystem
- SQL compatibility
- Supports vector search scenarios

Negative:

- Requires database configuration
- Scaling may require future evaluation
